    'Synthesis is the opposite of recap. A recap retells what you did; a synthesis tells the client what to do and why, in answer-first form. The test is whether a busy partner could act on your first sentence. "We analyzed costs, then revenue, then competitors" is a recap; "Cut the unprofitable product line, because it loses money on every unit and frees capacity for the growing line" is a synthesis.',
